snippet.textDisplay:
The caronavirus is not what theyre telling us it is

As im sure you guys know a new virus has been circulating recently. Covid-19 or catona virus as they've chosen to call it. Its a respiratory virus that starts with a mild cough, sore throat and other symptoms similar to the flu. When it progresses it can lead to pneumonia or bronchitis. If it progresses even further it can be very bad or even deadly. Wash your hands often and stay inside. General hygiene is enough it keep you from getting infected. Thats what they're telling. However.... that couldn't be further from the truth. I guess i should start from the beginning. I cant tell you my name because theyre watching me, waiting even now i know i dont have much time so im writing this to tell you the truth. When i was younger i had always dreamed of being a scientist. I gravitated towards it fron the very first episode of Dr. Who. Not only did i love science, i was good at it. I excelled and eventually got 3 phds by the time i was 30. Im gonna skip over the tedious details of how i got there but i found myself working for the government. I was apart of a top secret lab where we created everything from deadly illnesses for biological warfare to sprays that get rid of stains in an instant. It all started when we were working on with the rhinovirus. We discovered by using the cells of animals with regenerative properties we could cause the white blood cells to multiply and attack the virus with twice the power. Eliminating it much faster. We had been working on this for years and finaly after tons of work and millions in funding it was time for the first human testing. We took 4 perfectly healthy males and females. We gave all 4 of them the rhinovirus than We gave 1 male and 1 female the vaccine and ghe other two a placebo injection of saline.
After that there was nothing left to do. After a mere two days the two patients injected with the vaccine showed minimal symptoms and by the third tested negative for the rhino virus. This was a huge breakthrough! The lab was filled laughter and highfives all around. We told ourselves we deserved the rest of the day for celebration. I gave my number to the pacients for emergency and they were set up to return in two weeks for a check up where they would paid generously for participating in the experiment. There was cake and a few of us even had a glass of wine or two. Some of us took a much needed break for the next two weeks while the rest of us stayed behind to finalize the paperwork before submitting it to our supervisors. In the next two weeks the two pacients came back for there check up. There was something wrong. They were both horribly sick. They coughed and complained of chestpain and sore throats. Immediately we began work and test on the two to see what was wrong. My initial thought was that the vaccine had only worked temporarily but the rhinovirus had somehow survived and continued to infect the pacients. I would soon find out how wrong i was. The test came back within a few minutes. Me and my colleagues were dumbfounded as we checked the results. Negative for the rhinovirus. That was impossible. They showed all the symptoms, headaches sore throats dry caugh. We continued to test but they all came back negative. Whatever they had was completely new. My train of thought was interupted by a nurse running into the lab frantically telling us we had see what was happening. We ran to the quarantine room fast and what we saw still haunts me to this day. The male pacient justin was puking up a thick black viscous liquid on to the floor. The closest thing i could copare it to would be tar. We watched in horror as Justin than begin violently seezing on the floor. Just then the seezing stoped. Justin sat there on the floor and the heart rate monitor we affixed for testing was flatlined. He was dead. We couldnt do anything but watch in silence. But than it happened. His hand moved. But the heart monitor was still flatlined this was impossible. He slowly got up and turned toward the female pacient. Out of nowhere he charged ger. We all watched in horror as he not only attacked her but tore her appart with an inhuman strength. When he was done he turned and ran at the class in en effort to attack us. The glass cracked. I knew it wouldnt last much longet. This glass wasnt made to handle this kind of attack. I turned around and yelled for the officer waiting out side the door. As as he came and everyone yelled at him to shoot. Just as he had begun to assess the situation the glass broke. Immediately the room burst into chaos. Justin began attacking people. I ran and hid under the table. I didnt know what else to do. I watched as The police officer drew his pistol and shot the male pacient (if you vould even call it that) right in the the chest 3 times. But that seemed to only make it angrier. He shot it in the head as a last attempt to finally put that thing down. But it didnt work. It just continued to attack anything and everything nearby. I waited under the table and by some miracle it didnt notice me it walked out of the room presumably looking for something or someone else to tear apart. I took this as my time to run. I gtabbed my laptop and headed to my car. I went home. Its been two weeks and ive been in hiding. Im currently staying in a crappy motel in hong kong. Luckily my friend in the cybersecurity department gave me a machine that would act as a vpn for about 15 minutes when i said i wanted to be able to look at private things without the "upper management" knowing. I was able to use use this to keep tabbs on whats been going on . I know they are coming for me so im writing this up in hopes that if i send this out some of you will hear this. Its too late. They just announced the first American case. The virus is spreading it cant be stopped.im sitting here with the handgun my father gave me for christmas and a single bullet. I hope this message makes it to someone who cares. Not that it matters anymore. Goodbye
